\begin_layout Standard
Still the positive part is not zero and is showed in Fig.5.
 And these two figure prove that 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{res}$
\end_inset

 approach to the 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta(y)$
\end_inset

 in the zero skewness limit despite in different method.
 The result can be checked by the integral 
\begin_inset Formula $\int dyf=\int dy(f_{res}+\delta f)$
\end_inset

 which should be skewness independent and fit the form factors result in
 our previous work.
